detected: • FAILURE: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — 2 consecutive timeouts, delivery stopped • SESSION CLEANUP: 3 zombies from last state (cron:b653a6c0, cron:ac986a8d, subagent:8bffa95f) are now fully cleaned Pipeline: DEGRADED ⚠️ • Active sessions: 3 • MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅ • Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅ • Blockers: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — 2× timeout, needs review or disable — Orbis 🌐"}],"timestamp":1776184845141,"__openclaw":{"id":"cd9fad1e","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is to send a specific message to a Telegram group. I need to use the `message` tool to send this message to the Telegram channel. Let me check the available tools... \n\nLooking at the tools, I don't see a direct `message` tool. But I see there's a `tts` (text-to-speech) tool. However, that won't send a Telegram message.\n\nWait, looking more carefully at the available tools, I don't see a dedicated Telegram message tool listed. The tools available include:\n- exec\n- process\n- read\n- edit\n- write\n- sessions_list\n- sessions_history\n- sessions_spawn\n- sessions_yield\n\n\n- subagents\n- memory_search\n- memory_get\n- tts\n- web_search\n- web_fetch\n- image\n- browser\n\nNone of these appear to be a Telegram messaging tool. Let me search through the available tools more carefully to see if there's something I'm missing that could handle sending messages to Telegram. I'm realizing I don't have access to a dedicated Telegram messaging tool in this environment—the available tools are primarily for browsing, file operations, and session management, none of which handle external messaging like Telegram. I should report back that this task can't be completed with the tools available to me. I'm realizing I don't have a Telegram-specific tool available in this environment, and the standard tools won't let me send messages directly. I need to be straightforward that this task can't be completed with what's